<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900918-0155</DOCNO><DOCID>900918-0155.</DOCID><HL>   Canada Will Offer   $1.4 Billion in Bonds   In Four Maturities</HL><DATE>09/18/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C16</SO><CO>   CANDA</CO><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)</IN><LP>   OTTAWA -- The Canadian government said it will offer 1.6billion Canadian dollars (US$1.4 billion) of government bondsin four maturities this week.   The sale will involve 10.25% bonds due Feb. 1, 1994;10.25% bonds due March 1, 1996; 10.5% bonds due March 1,2001; 11.25% bonds due June 1, 2015. Offering terms are to beannounced today. The Bank of Canada agreed to purchase atleast C$100 million of the new bonds. The remainder will beavailable to public investors.</LP><TEXT>   Proceeds of the issue will be used to redeem C$1.1 billionof government bonds maturing Oct. 1 and for generalgovernment purposes.</TEXT></DOC>